	As of December 31, 2016, our investments in real estate of $854,646 were financed through $186,237 of mortgage loans or other debt held by third parties and $642,824 of mortgage loans held by our RAIT I and RAIT II CDO securitizations.  As of December 31, 2015, our investments in real estate of $1,145,630 were financed through $269,790 of mortgage loans held by third parties and $851,711 of mortgage loans held by our RAIT I and RAIT II CDO securitizations.  Together, along with commercial real estate loans held by RAIT I and RAIT II, these mortgages serve as collateral for the CDO notes payable issued by the RAIT I and RAIT II CDO securitizations. All intercompany balances and interest charges are eliminated in consolidation.


	 


